# L-{{NUMBER}} — OAuth secret malformed by a pipe chain (even invisibly)

**Date:** {{DATE_YYYY_MM_DD}}
**PR:** #{{PR_NUMBER}}
**Affected layers:** EXT-5 Scripts, EXT-9 Infra (GitHub Secrets)
**Severity:** high (blocks the CI Claude review for hours/days until found)

> **Native shortcut:** `/install-github-app` (OAuth) avoids this whole class of
> bug — it sets the secret through the GitHub API, so no shell pipe ever touches
> the token bytes. The `setup-oauth-secret.sh` wrapper below is now the fallback
> (re-setting the secret, self-hosted CI). This lesson stays as the diagnosis
> for when a secret was set the hard way.

## Symptom (P1)

The `claude-review` job in `pr-auto-review.yml` fails consistently with:

```
error: Claude Code returned an error result:
Failed to authenticate. API Error: 401 Invalid bearer token
```

Meanwhile, a direct `curl` to the Anthropic API with the SAME token returns HTTP
200:

```bash
curl -sS https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages \
  -H "authorization: Bearer sk-ant-oat01-..." \
  -H "anthropic-version: 2023-06-01" \
  -H "content-type: application/json" \
  -d '{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","max_tokens":10,"messages":[{"role":"user","content":"hi"}]}'
# HTTP_200
```

The token is technically valid, but the `anthropics/claude-code-action` SDK
rejects it.

## Investigation

Descending hierarchy P1 → P5:

- **P1 (symptom):** consistent 401 across N runs, always `Invalid bearer
  token`, NOT `Workflow validation failed` (that's a different 401 — this one
  is the SDK validating the bearer).
- **P2 (logs):** message from the action's SDK, coming from the bundled JS
  code. `App token exchange` shows OK on some runs, but the actual API call
  is rejected.
- **P3 (secret):** `gh secret list` shows a recent `updatedAt`. You can't read
  the value (GitHub doesn't expose it).
- **P4 (workflow):** correct input (`claude_code_oauth_token`), `@v1` version,
  default bot_id/bot_name. Config identical to another repo where the same
  token works — it's not the workflow.
- **Surgical refutation:** setting the SAME token in another repo via a direct
  stdin redirect (`< /tmp/token.bin`) makes the action pass. Confirmation: the
  setting method is the cause.

## Root cause

`gh secret set ... --body -` chains receive everything that comes in on stdin,
including invisible bytes: `\n` injected by `echo`, a UTF-8 BOM from
`base64 -d`, surrogates from `tr`, residual whitespace from `read VAR`. The
GitHub API accepts and stores the literal value (it doesn't normalize). The
secret ends up with extra bytes.

When the workflow injects the secret into `$CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN`, the SDK's
HTTP header becomes:

```
authorization: Bearer sk-ant-oat01-...AA\n
                                          ^ newline
```

The Anthropic API is tolerant via curl (the HTTP layer accepts it), but the
Claude Code SDK strictly validates the shape of the bearer header and rejects
any non-token char before the call reaches the API.

## Fix

ALWAYS set the secret via a **binary-file stdin redirect**, with no intermediate
pipe:

```bash
# Save the token to a binary file (umask 077)
printf '%s' "$TOKEN" > /tmp/oauth.bin
chmod 600 /tmp/oauth.bin

# Check the size (sk-ant-oat01- yields 108 bytes; the value may change)
wc -c < /tmp/oauth.bin  # expected: CLEAN_BYTE_COUNT

# Set via stdin redirect — zero transformation
gh secret set CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN -R OWNER/REPO < /tmp/oauth.bin

# Clean up
rm /tmp/oauth.bin
```

Canonical wrapper in the project: `scripts/setup-oauth-secret.sh` (template
`templates/scripts/setup-oauth-secret.sh.template` of the
`setup-projeto-qualidade` skill).

## Prevention going forward

- [x] **Native path** `/install-github-app` (OAuth): sets the secret through
  the GitHub API, no shell pipe in the path. Primary recommendation.
- [x] **Canonical wrapper** `scripts/setup-oauth-secret.sh` (fallback) that:
  - reads from the macOS Keychain or an env var (zero pipe)
  - writes to a binary file (`printf '%s' "$TOKEN" > file`)
  - validates the `sk-ant-oat01-` prefix + size + last char
  - sets via `gh secret set ... < file`
  - cleans the file on `trap`
- [x] **Optional diagnostic step** in the workflow:
  ```yaml
  - name: Diag oauth token length
    run: |
      echo "len=${#CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN}"
      # 108 = sk-ant-oat01-* well-formed; >108 = malformed
  ```
- [x] **Explicit doc** in the skill's `Claude authentication (OAuth-first)`:
  NEVER use `echo $TOK | gh secret set --body -`. ALWAYS via a file + stdin
  redirect.

## When this lesson applies

- Setting any byte-sensitive secret (OAuth tokens, JWT, private keys) in GitHub
  Secrets via the CLI.
- Diagnosing an inexplicable 401 where a direct curl works but the action fails.
- Migrating from an API key (which tolerates a trailing newline by HTTP
  convention) to OAuth (which does not).

## Reusable pattern

**Strict bearer validation ≠ historical HTTP tolerance.** Modern SDKs
(Anthropic, OpenAI, Stripe) validate the bearer header shape BEFORE making a
request. A header with residual whitespace = 401 without ever leaving the
machine. `curl` is tolerant for historical compatibility. Any automation that
sets a secret programmatically MUST use a binary-safe channel (file stdin
redirect, not a pipe).

